# Neural correlates of attention bias in posttraumatic stress disorder
**Autores**: Noa Herz
**Año**: 2016
**Journal**: Clinical Neurophysiology, 127 (2016) 3268-3276. doi:10.1016/j.clinph.2016.07.016
**DOI/Link**: N/A

## Abstract
Not found

## Key Findings
Discussion
The present study investigated the neural correlates of the
altered P3 activity observed in PTSD patients in response to target
tones and distractors in the auditory oddball paradigm. During the
standard trials PTSD patients showed hyperactivity in the dlPFC,
while having reduced dlPFC activity during the infrequent stimuli
(targets and distractors) relative to controls (Figs. 3 and 4). PTSD
